</FONT><B><FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=4><P>Basic Laws of Indices</P></B></FONT>
<FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=2>
<P>It is important that you are confident in the manipulation of algebraic expressions where the variable is raised to a power.   
In <B>linear</B> expressions the <B>power is 1</B> and in <B>quadratic</B> expressions the <B>power is 2</B>.  However there are expressions where the power may be greater than 2 or less than 1 or fractional !   </P>

<P>Work through <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 14 a~?">1-14 section a</a>, <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 14 b 0~?">section b</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 14 c 0~?">section c</a>.
Examples are detailed in your lecture notes pages 15 and 16.</P>

<P>Now spend time on <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 24 a 0~?">1-24 section a</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 24 b 0~?">section b</a>.   Try <a href="launch.htm#q0388">q0388</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0392">q0392</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0389">q0389</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0591">q0591</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0390">q0390</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0391">q0391</a> and <a href="launch.htm#q0386">q0386</a>.</P>

<P>Simplify expressions which have fractional powers in <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 24 c 0~?">1-24 section c</a>, <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 24 d 0~?">section d</a>, <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 24 e 0~?">section e</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 24 f 0~?">section f</a>.    More detail and examples are given on pages 20 and 21 of your lecture notes.</P>

